dany (1.2.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Flag parsing: both CLIs migrate from jessevdk/go-flags to
    alecthomas/kong, bringing the project in line with the standard Go
    CLI stack. --help output structure now follows kong's conventions
    (Arguments / Flags sections, =STRING placeholders); the runtime
    "Default/Supported types" footer is preserved via a kong.Help hook
    in both CLIs. dany still accepts its two deprecated positional-arg
    forms (@<ip> server, bare <RR>[,<RR>...] types list) with the same
    runtime deprecation warning as before.

  * Coloured --help: integrated github.com/gavincarr/kong-help-colours
    so --help emits yellow section headers, green flag tokens, and cyan
    placeholders when stdout is a TTY and NO_COLOR is unset. Falls back
    to the default plain printer otherwise, so piped/non-TTY help output
    is byte-identical.

 -- Gavin Carr <gavin@openfusion.net>  Wed, 27 May 2026 12:21:28 +0800

dany (1.1.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Logging: both CLIs switch from a bespoke vprintf/verbose-bool to
    log/slog with github.com/lmittmann/tint, matching the standard Go
    CLI stack. -v now counts: bare -v enables Info, -vv enables Debug;
    default level is Warn so nothing is printed without -v. dnx's
    per-hostname "looking up" line drops to Debug so bulk stdin runs
    aren't flooded with one info line per host.

  * Testability: extracted runCLI(opts, io.Writer) from both main()
    functions. opts/parser are no longer package-level state, errors
    propagate as return values instead of log.Fatal mid-flow, and the
    renderer writes through a caller-supplied io.Writer so end-to-end
    tests capture output into a bytes.Buffer rather than exec'ing the
    binary. Five new offline end-to-end tests cover dany text/JSON
    rendering + -o override and dnx NXDOMAIN/Count modes.

  * Packaging: new scripts/deb_tarball.sh wraps the local source tree
    into dist/deb/dany_<version>.tar.gz — stripped static binaries +
    debian/ + LICENCE + README, ready for `dpkg-buildpackage -b` on a
    build machine. Version is read from debian/changelog via
    dpkg-parsechangelog (same single source of truth as
    scripts/release.sh), and a fresh CGO_ENABLED=0 / -buildvcs=false
    build is forced so the static-binary guarantees are applied.

 -- Gavin Carr <gavin@openfusion.net>  Mon, 25 May 2026 15:53:21 +0800

dany (1.0.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * New flag: -w/--www. Probes the www.<hostname> label in addition to
    the apex. Defaults to A+AAAA, but honors an explicit -t/--types or
    -a/--all (so `dany -w -t mx` queries MX against www. too). In
    tagged mode (-T), apex and www results are emitted on separate
    hostname-tagged lines; in untagged mode they share the output and
    identical rows are deduped, so a www that resolves to the apex IP
    doesn't appear twice. Render also dedups identical lines
    unconditionally now — only observable when -w introduces duplicates.

  * New flag: -f/--fmt {text,json,yaml,yml}. Adds structured output
    alongside the default tab-separated text. Each record carries both
    `rdata` (DNS presentation form) and a typed `data` payload — e.g.
    `{preference, exchange}` for MX, full RFC field set for SOA,
    `{strings: [...]}` for TXT. A versioned envelope (schema_version: 1)
    wraps the per-hostname output; multi-host runs emit NDJSON (json
    mode) or multi-document YAML (yaml mode, `---`-separated). In
    structured modes, errors fold into the envelope's `errors` field
    with a stable machine-readable `code` (NXDOMAIN, SERVFAIL,
    EXCHANGE_ERROR, UNSUPPORTED_TYPE) — nothing goes to stderr. PTR
    records (with -p/--ptr) appear as standalone entries with the
    source IP carried in `data.ip` for easy joining (text mode folds
    them into the matching A/AAAA row as before). `yml` is a
    convenience alias for `yaml`.

  * New flag: --version on both `dany` and `dnx`. Long-only (`dnx`
    already uses -V for --invert); short-circuits print `<name>
    <version>` and exits before any other validation, so it works
    without other required arguments.

  * Library: errors from RunQuery / RunNXQuery are now *QueryError
    (Type, Hostname, Code, Err) instead of fmt.Errorf-wrapped strings.
    Error() preserves the historical message format and Unwrap exposes
    the underlying sentinel so errors.Is(err, ErrNXDomain/ErrServFail)
    continues to work for existing consumers.

  * Build: scripts/build_all.sh now exports CGO_ENABLED=0 so the
    resulting binaries are unconditionally pure-Go static (no libc /
    NSS resolver linkage), matching the Debian package description.
    Also passes -buildvcs=false so VCS metadata isn't baked in and
    commit-to-commit builds stay byte-stable.

  * Release flow: internal/version/VERSION is the single source of
    truth for the version string, //go:embed'd into both binaries.
    `scripts/release.sh <version>` syncs it with debian/changelog,
    commits, and annotated-tags; the changelog is the structural gate
    (no stanza, no release).

 -- Gavin Carr <gavin@openfusion.net>  Mon, 25 May 2026 13:20:47 +0800

dany (0.1.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial Debian packaging.
  * Ships two binaries: `dany` (DNS lookup tool that simulates ANY queries
    by firing typed RR lookups concurrently and aggregating results, with
    text/JSON/YAML output formats) and `dnx` (concurrent NXDOMAIN bulk
    prober for hostname lists).

 -- Gavin Carr <gavin@openfusion.net>  Mon, 25 May 2026 12:41:24 +0800
